page.title: 09 Launceston Police Station
page.content: Launceston Police Station employs 32 people who are in the force,and 10 other civilians. There are 20 constables,10 sergeants,1 inspector and 1 Chief Inspector in the station. The policemen and women work in shifts These are from 6 am to 2 pm:2 pm to 10 pm and from 10pm to 6 am. There are 6 cells and 2 detention rooms.There is also a pooltable and a bar for when the policemen are off duty.Most crimes in the area are committed in the summer because that is when most visitors are around. The station has a canteen and rooms for unmarried people There are also police houses nearby.The station does not hve any animals but it has squad cars.They have small breathalizers and a computer called Lion 3,000 for measuring the alcohol levels in the blood.
